"subtopic": "5. A. Multiple Choice Questions",
"content": "3. The SI unit of moment of a force is 4. For a given moment of a force, the magnitude of the force applied can be reduced by 6. Eight or more wheels are provided in a heavy truck. This is done\n\n**Must know**\n• Moment of the force, tau = F × d = 2.5 N × 0.4 m = 1.0 N m.\n• Torque (moment of a force), tau = F × d = 12 N × 0.25 m = 3.0 N m.\n• Here, force, F = 12 N and moment of a force, tau = 4.2 N m.\n• Moment~of~a~force=F_1 × d_1=8 N × 0.18 m=1.44 N m.\n• Distance,d_2=Moment of a force/F_2=1.44N m/6N=0.24m or24cm.\n• Press both the pins down with equal force with the help of a flat wooden piece.\n• Heavy vehicles like trucks and trawlers are fitted with eight or more wheels so that the area of contact with the ground is increased and pressure is reduced.\n• Thrust acting on unit area is called pressure.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Eight or more wheels are provided in a heavy truck.\n• Pressure at a point inside the liquid increases with the depth from the free surface of the liquid.\n• Heavy vehicles like trucks and trawlers are fitted with eight or more wheels so that the area of contact with the ground is increased and pressure is reduced.\n• Bigger the area, lesser will be the effect of a force.\n• Both A and R are true, but R is not the correct explanation of A\n• Here, force, F = 12 N and moment of a force, tau = not N m.\n• Fill: Eight or more wheels — Eight or more wheels are provided in a heavy truck.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• **Atmospheric pressure** — associated with : Pressure exerted by the atmospheric air\n• **Pressure** — associated with : The normal force (thrust) acting per unit surface area\n• **Thrust** — associated with : The total normal force exerted by an object on a given surface\n• **Torque** — associated with : Turning moment of a force about the pivot point (axis of rotation)\n\nAlso revise:\n• Pressure may also be defined as thrust per unit area.\n• Its actual value is 1.013 × 10^5 Pa.\n• Atmospheric pressure is maximum at sea level.\n• Eight or more wheels are provided in a heavy truck.",
