"content": "In the questions given below, there are two statements marked as Assertion [A] and Reason [R]. Read the statements and choose the correct option for each 1. Assertion: Pressure is a scalar quantity Reason: Pressure does not have any direction\n\n**Must know**\n• Cycling of a bicycle: During cycling his bicycle, a cyclist applies a force on the pedal using his foot.\n• Reason is defined as Pressure does not have any direction.\n• Assertion: A girl applies force using her foot on the pedal of a bicycle.\n• Reason: The pedal turns about the pedal.\n• Reason is defined as The pedal turns about the pedal.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Cycling of a bicycle: During cycling his bicycle, a cyclist applies a force on the pedal using his foot.\n• Reason: The pedal turns about the pedal.\n• Fill: During — Cycling of a bicycle: During cycling his bicycle, a cyclist applies a force on the pedal using his f\n• Fill: Pressure — Reason: Pressure does not have any direction.",
