"type": "note",
"subtopic": "8. D. State whether the following statements are true or false. If false, rewrite the correct form of statements",
"content": "2. The moment of a force increases on decreasing the perpendicular distance between force and axis of rotation 3. We prefer to use a long spanner to loosen a tight nut 4. Steering wheel of a car is used to accelerate the car\n\n**Must know**\n• Liquids and gases exert pressure in all directions.\n• Moment of the force propto Perpendicular distance (d).\n• Torque, tau = Force(F) × perpendicular distance(d).\n• Here, force, F = 2.5 N and perpendicular distance, d = 40 cm = 0.4 m.\n• Press both the pins down with equal force with the help of a flat wooden piece.\n• Your school bag and shopping bag have broad straps so as to reduce pressure on your hands or on the shoulders.\n• Similarly, pillars of bridges, flyovers and overhead metro train tracks have a broad base so as to reduce pressure on the ground.\n• A camel can walk easily even on sandy surfaces because it has broad feet and hence it exerts less pressure.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Pressure is exerted by solids, liquids as well as gases.\n• Thrust acting on unit area is called pressure.\n• Both A and R are true, and R is the correct explanation of A\n• Both A and R are true, but R is not the correct explanation of A\n• Liquids and gases exert not in all directions.\n• Fill: Steering wheel of a car — Steering wheel of a car is used to accelerate the car.\n• Fill: Perpendicular — Moment of the force propto Perpendicular distance (d).",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• **Pressure** — associated with : The normal force (thrust) acting per unit surface area\n• **Torque** — associated with : Turning moment of a force about the pivot point (axis of rotation)\n\nAlso revise:\n• Liquids not only exert pressure on the bottom of the container, but also exert pressure on the walls of the container.\n• State whether the following statements are true or false.\n• Steering wheel of a car is used to accelerate the car.\n• Pillars of bridges have broad bases so as to reduce pressure on the ground.",
