"subtopic": "1. Introduction",
"content": "Hands-on Learning · Critical Thinking display a scientific attitude while making models communicate logical reasoning and explanations effectively using scientific terms\n\n**Must know**\n• Speed of light is extraordinarily large at 3 × 10^8 m/s in vacuum or air.\n• Finally, you will study the action of a prism and dispersion caused by a prism.\n• Light travels with a constant speed of 3 × 10^8 m/s in vacuum and air.\n• Refractive index of a medium is the ratio of speed of light in vacuum (or air) and speed of light in the given medium.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Speed of light is extraordinarily large at 3 × 10^8 m/s in vacuum or air.\n• Remove the pins and the glass slab.\n• Communicate logical not and explanations effectively using scientific terms.\n• Finally, you will study the action of a prism and dispersion caused by a prism.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• **Dispersion** — associated with : Splitting of white light into its constituent seven colours on passing through a dispersive medium, e.g., a glass prism\n• **Prism** — associated with : A transparent material bound by two plane refracting faces inclined at an angle\n• **Refractive index** — associated with : The ratio of speed of light in air (or vacuum) to the speed of light of the given medium\n• **Light** — a form of energy which travels in a straight line\n• **Speed of light** — extraordinarily large at 3 × 10^8 m/s in vacuum or air",
"source": "icse",
"examTip": "Read in order, then tap Practice linked questions — notes cover what exam questions ask.",
