"subtopic": "5. Terms Related to Spherical Mirrors",
"content": "Look at a spherical mirror MPM' as shown in Fig. 5.8 The spherical mirror is a part of a hollow sphere. Now, understand the terms related to the spherical mirror Pole: The geometric centre (P) of a spherical mirror is called its pole\n\n**Must know**\n• Normal: A line drawn at the point of incidence and perpendicular to the surface media is called the normal.\n• Centre of curvature: It is the centre (C) of the sphere of which the spherical mirror forms.\n• Centre of curvature is defined as It is the centre (C) of the sphere of which the spherical mirror forms.\n• Radius of curvature: It is the radius of the sphere of which the spherical mirror forms a pa So, the distance between the pole and the centre of curvature of a mirror is equal to its radius.\n• Radius of curvature is defined as It is the radius of the sphere of which the spherical mirror forms a pa So, the distance between the pole and the centre of curvature of a mirror is equal to its radius.\n• Principal axis: The imaginary line passing through the pole and the centre of curvature (PCX) is called the principal axis of the mirror.\n• Principal axis is defined as The imaginary line passing through the pole and the centre of curvature (PCX) is called the principal axis of the mirror.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Principal axis is defined as The imaginary line passing through the pole and the centre of curvature (PCX) is called the principal axis of t\n• Fill: Radius of curvature: It — Radius of curvature: It is the radius of the sphere of which the spherical mirror forms a pa So, the",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• **Spherical mirror** — associated with : A slice taken out from a hollow glass sphere and silvered on one side so that reflection takes place from the other side\n• **Point of incidence** — defined as The point at which the incident ray enters the second medium is called the point of incidence. In , point O is the point of incidence\n• **Normal** — defined as A line drawn at the point of incidence and perpendicular to the surface media is called the normal. In , N_1ON_2 is the normal\n\nAlso revise:\n• Aperture: The length MM' of the perimeter of the spherical mirror is called its aperture.\n• Aperture is defined as The length MM' of the perimeter of the spherical mirror is called its aperture.\n• Focal length: The distance between the pole and the principal focus of a mirror is called its focal length and is expressed as f.\n• Focal length is defined as The distance between the pole and the principal focus of a mirror is called its focal length and is expressed as f.",
