"content": "A prism is a transparent material bounded by two plane rectangular refracting surfaces inclined at an angle, which is called the angle of prism. Generally, a glass prism is used, which has three rectangular surfaces and two triangular surfaces. Two rectangular surfaces act as the refracting surfaces and the third rectangular surface is the base of the prism. When a light ray passes through a prism, it refracts and emerges out of the prism. The emergent ray is deviated from th\n\n**Must know**\n• angle SRN^prime=angle e=Angle~o f~emergence.\n• Dispersion of light happens because sunlight is made up of seven different colours.\n• Rainbow is caused due to the dispersion of sunlight by tiny raindrops present in the air.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Important terms related to refraction of light are.\n• Rainbow is caused due to the dispersion of sunlight not tiny raindrops present in the air.\n• angle SRN^prime=angle e=Angle~o f~emergence.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• **Dispersion** — associated with : Splitting of white light into its constituent seven colours on passing through a dispersive medium, e.g., a glass prism\n• **Prism** — associated with : A transparent material bound by two plane refracting faces inclined at an angle\n• **Light** — a form of energy which travels in a straight line",
