"subtopic": "19. H. Match the position of an object and characteristics of image formed by a concave mirror",
"content": "1. At C (a) Real, inverted and diminished image formed between F and C 2. At infinity (b) Virtual, erect and enlarged image formed behind the mirror 3. At F (c) Real, inverted and of same size at C\n\n**Must know**\n• S. No. relates to Position of the object, Position of the image, and Size of the image.\n• Beyond C relates to Between F and C, Diminished, and Real and inverted.\n• Between C and F relates to Beyond C, Enlarged, and Real and inverted.\n• Between F and P relates to Behind the mirror, Enlarged, and Virtual and erected.\n• Real images formed by a concave mirror.\n• Here, we are discussing following five cases in which the image formed is a real image.\n• Case 1: When the object is placed at infinity.\n• Case 1 is defined as When the object is placed at infinity. The image formed is real and inverted.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Material medium relates to Refractive index, Material medium, and Refractive index.\n• Conclusion: The curved inner surface of polished spoon acts as a concave mirror but the curved outer surface behaves as a convex mirror.\n• Beyond C relates to Between F and C, Diminished, and Real and inverted.\n• Generally, a real and inverted image is formed by a concave mirror except when the object is placed between the principal focus not the pole\n• Image formed by a concave mirror is always.\n• Between P and F (f) Real, inverted and highly enlarged image at infinity.",
