"subtopic": "8. Activity 6 SEL Self-Awareness",
"content": "There are various applications of thermal expansion of acids, liquids and gases. Some important ones are: 1. While laying rail tracks, a small gap is left between two successive rails to make room for thermal expansion. If it is not done, the rail may bend due to thermal expansion in summer and it may cause accidents 2 Concrete floors are laid in small blocks with small gaps between the blocks. It allows expansion of blocks during summer and the floor does not crack\n\n**Must know**\n• Vaporisation takes place due to the following two phenomena.\n• Although in both evaporation and boiling processes, a substance changes from liquid state to the vapour (or gaseous) state, the two processes differ in the following respects.\n• Evaporation process takes place at all temperatures but boiling process takes place at a fixed temperature, called the boiling point of liquid only.\n• Evaporation is a surface phenomenon only but boiling takes place throughout the liquid simultaneously.\n• After fitting, cold water is poured on them, so that, they contract and grip the wheel tightly.\n• Bimetallic strips are used in thermostats to automatically control the temperature in electric irons, electric ovens, geysers, refrigerators, etc.\n• Steel girders supporting a bridge are mounted on the rollers rather than being fixed in the walls of the pillars.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Here, original length of the cable, L = 30 m.\n• Tyres of vehicles are filled with less air during summer to accommodate the expansion of air in them, when the car is driven on the road.\n• Conclusion: The iron ball expands on heating and contracts on cooling.\n• Metal pipes used for carrying steam have joints in the form of loops.\n• Expansion in volume of any substance on heating expansion.\n• Evaporation process takes place at all temperatures but boiling process takes place at a fixed temperature, called the boiling point of liqu",
