"subtopic": "11. D. State whether the following statements are true or false. If false, rewrite the correct form of statements",
"content": "1. All solids expand equally when heated to same rise in temperature 2. Coefficient of superficial expansion of a solid is twice the linear expansion coefficient of the same solid 3. Telephone wires are intentionally kept slightly loose between the poles at the time of laying them\n\n**Must know**\n• Evaporation: It is the process where a liquid changes into its vapour form at any temperature, but it only happens at the surface of the liquid.\n• Conclusion: For same rise (or fall) in temperature, different solids expand or contract differently.\n• There are two different processes through which vaporisation of liquids takes place.\n• State whether the following statements are true or false.\n• A small gap is left between two successive rails to make room for thermal expansion.\n• Expansion coefficient of pyrex glass is much more than that of ordinary glass.\n• Mercury expands on heating but alcohol contracts on heating.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• State whether the following statements are true or false.\n• Explanation of thermal expansion of solids on the basis of molecular motion.\n• Here, coefficient of linear expansion of steel, alpha = 1.1 × 10^-5/^circC.\n• Both A and R are true, and R is the correct explanation of A\n• Both A and R are true, but R is not the correct explanation of A\n• Fill: Telephone wires — Telephone wires are intentionally kept slightly loose between the poles at the time of laying them.",
