"content": "In previous classes, you have learnt about 'sound'. Sound is a form of energy which causes sensation of hearing in our ears. Let us recollect some important facts about sound. These are as follows: Sound is produced by the vibration of objects. As long as the source of sound continues to vibrate, sound will be produced. Different types of instruments and devices are used to produce sound 》 In humans, sound is produced by the voice box (larynx) located\n\n**Must know**\n• Sound needs a medium for its propagation.\n• Sound travels with a finite speed in the given material medium.\n• Speed of sound is maximum in solids, less in liquids and the least in gases.\n• Number~o f~oscillations~completed~i n~time~T=1~.\n• Sound is a form of energy which can propagate through a material medium only.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• 》 In humans, sound is produced by the voice box (larynx) located.\n• Sound energy is propagated as a wave.\n• Speed of sound is maximum in solids, less in liquids and the least in gases.",
