"content": "a longitudinal sound wave is propagated gh a medium, the density as well as the re of the medium at a given time vary with\n\n**Must know**\n• Now discuss some important characteristics of a sound wave.\n• Amplitude is usually represented by the symbol A.\n• Wavelength ( lambda) may also be defined as the distance travelled by the wave during one oscillation period (or time period T) of a medium particle.\n• Distance between two consecutive compressions = distance between two consecutive rarefactions = lambda, and distance between a compression and an adjacent rarefaction = lambda/2.\n• Wavelength: The distance between two consecutive compressions or two consecutive rarefactions is called the wavelength.\n• Hertz (1857–1894) was a German physicist and studied at University of Berlin.\n• He experimentally confirmed Maxwell's electromagnetic wave theory.\n• Frequency is usually represented by symbol v (Greek letter nu).\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• Sound in air travels as a wave.\n• Wave speed is usually denoted by symbol v.\n• A particular sound may appear to be quite loud to one person but not so loud to another person.\n• Now discuss some important characteristics of a sound wave.\n• Hertz (1857–1894) was a German physicist and studied at University of Berlin.\n• A longitudinal wave travels in the form of alternate compressions and rarefactions.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• **Sound** — a form of energy which causes sensation of hearing in our ears\n• **Speed of sound** — maximum in solids, less in liquids and the least in gases\n• **Amplitude** — usually represented by the symbol A\n• **Frequency** — usually represented by symbol v (Greek letter nu)\n\nAlso revise:\n• Time period: The time taken between two consecutive compressions or rarefactions crossing a point is called the time period of the wave.\n• Alternately, the time taken for one complete oscillation in the density (or pressure) of the medium is called the time period of the wave.\n• Time period is usually represented by the symbol T.\n• (f) Wave speed: The wave speed of sound waves is defined as the distance which a point of a wave, such as a compression or a rarefaction, travels per unit time.",
