"content": "The loudness of a sound depends on the following factors: Loudness mainly depends on the amplitude of vibration: It is observed that greater the amplitude, louder is the sound produced. When you whisper, you use very less energy and amplitude of vibration of your vocal cords is small. So, the sound produced is very weak. When you shout, you use more energy and amplitude of vibration of your vocal cords is large. As a result, a loud sound is produced\n\n**Must know**\n• Energy level of sound (in W/m^2) relates to 10^-12, 10^-11, and 10^-10.\n• Sound is produced by the vibration of objects.\n• Sound energy is propagated as a wave.\n• First, pluck the thick wire at the middle and listen the sound produced.\n• Loudness of a sound mainly depends on the amplitude of vibration of the sound source.\n• State the factors on which loudness of a sound depends.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• State the factors on which frequency of sound produced by a string instrument depends.\n• Loudness mainly depends on the amplitude of vibration: It is observed that greater the amplitude, louder is the sound produced.\n• Sound energy is propagated as a wave.\n• Fill: Sound energy — Sound energy is propagated as a wave.\n• Match each term with its correct description.\n• So, the sound produced is very weak.",
