"subtopic": "7. Simple Rules for the Safe Use of Electricity at Home",
"content": "Electricity is a very good source of energy and it helps in making our life easier and comfortable if used properly and carefully. But, electrical energy is very dangerous too, if not used properly and carefully. Although various electrical devices and circuits have been designed in such a way that the safety of the consumer is ensured, yet one should be very alert while using an electrical device. One should take the following precautions: ISI mark is given by Indian Bureau\n\n**Must know**\n• 1 Do not put your finger or metallic object in a socket.\n• I Never play with electric wires, switches, plugs, sockets, etc.\n• 1 Always wear rubber slippers while working on electrical appliances.\n• 1 Give proper earthing to the sockets.\n• 1 Use only ISI marked electrical appliances.\n• Similarly, ebonite rod when rubbed with a funnel or wool also shows the property of attracting small bits of paper and straw.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• 1 Always wear rubber slippers while working on electrical appliances.\n• 1 Do not touch electric poles during rainy season, as leakage of current may take place and it may give you a shock.\n• Although various electrical devices and circuits have been designed in such a way that the safety of the consumer is ensured, yet one should be very alert…",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• **Electricity** — supplied to our houses via overhead wires (or cables) on poles or underground cables made of copper or aluminium\n\nAlso revise:\n• Rubbing with some other objects acquire the property of attracting tiny objects are said to be electrified objects or charged objects.\n• Remove your finger and then remove the ebonite rod too.\n• Unplug all electrical appliances like your computer, TV set, etc.",
"source": "icse",
