"topicId": "ch8-electricity",
"type": "note",
"subtopic": "26. Make your own solar furnace",
"content": "Take a small pudding plate of stainless steel, a plastic straw, cellotape and some candle wax Hold the pudding plate out in an open space but close to a wall, on a hot afternoon Tilt the plate so that it faces the sun and try to focus the sunlight on the wall\n\n**Must know**\n• Alternately, you may take a light and small styrofoam ball.\n• Measure the distance between the wall and the pudding plate.\n• Scratch a waste metallic key with sand paper and tie it with one of the free ends of the connecting wire as shown in the figure.\n• Your water heater is ready to be used.\n• Light the bulb and hold the steel bowl behind it.\n• Your searchlight is now ready to work.\n• Place the beaker on a table and pour refined oil in it.\n• So, refraction of light does not take place and hence the immersed part of the rod is not visible to us.\n\n**Answers for linked questions**\n• So, refraction of light does not take place and hence the immersed part of the rod is not visible to us.",
"explanation": "",
"source": "icse",
